---

## 1. Design Principles

| Principle | What it means |
|---|---|
| **Breathability** | Generous whitespace between sections. No cramped layouts. Content feels open and calm. |
| **Soft depth** | Very subtle shadows (low blur, low opacity). Cards float gently, never pop aggressively. |
| **Restrained color** | One accent gradient for hero cards. Everything else is neutral with tinted pastels for status/icons. |
| **Consistent rhythm** | Same spacing, same radius, same padding everywhere. Visual consistency = perceived quality. |
| **Purposeful motion** | Subtle transitions (fade, slide-up) on page load and state changes. Nothing bouncy or playful. |

---

## 2. Color Palette Refinement

### Current → Proposed changes

Your existing palette in `theme.dart` is already quite good. The refinements are minor and focused on warmth and elegance:

```diff
 // Core accent palette — KEEP (already elegant)
 static const Color primaryColor = Color(0xFF465FFF);
 static const Color primaryDark = Color(0xFF3448D9);
 static const Color primaryLight = Color(0xFF9CB0FF);

 // Card gradient — KEEP (signature look)
 static const Color cardPrimaryStart = Color(0xFF1D4ED8);
 static const Color cardPrimaryEnd = Color(0xFF465FFF);

-// Surfaces and backgrounds
-static const Color backgroundColor = Color(0xFFF4F7FC);
+// Surfaces and backgrounds — slightly warmer for elegance
+static const Color backgroundColor = Color(0xFFF5F7FA);
 
-static const Color cardSurface = Color(0xFFF7F9FF);
+static const Color cardSurface = Color(0xFFFFFFFF);  // Pure white cards

+// NEW: Elevated surface for active/hover states
+static const Color cardSurfaceElevated = Color(0xFFF8FAFF);

-static const Color cardBorder = Color(0xFFDDE5FF);
+static const Color cardBorder = Color(0xFFE8ECF4);  // Softer, less blue

+// NEW: Skeleton/shimmer colors
+static const Color shimmerBase = Color(0xFFEEF1F6);
+static const Color shimmerHighlight = Color(0xFFF8FAFC);
```

### Additions needed

| Token | Value | Purpose |
|---|---|---|
| `surfaceOverlay` | `Color(0x0A465FFF)` | Very faint blue tint for hover/pressed states |
| `cardShadow` | `Color(0x0A111827)` | Shadow color (4% black) — softer than current |
| `borderSubtle` | `Color(0xFFF0F2F5)` | Even lighter border for info sections |

> [!TIP]
> The key shift: Move cards from `#F7F9FF` (blueish tint) to **pure white** `#FFFFFF`. This creates a cleaner contrast against the `#F5F7FA` background and looks much more premium on-device.

---

## 3. Typography Adjustments

Your `Outfit` font + text theme is solid. Small refinements for elegance:

| Level | Current | Proposed | Why |
|---|---|---|---|
| `headlineLarge` | `32px, -0.6 ls` | `30px, -0.5 ls` | Slightly less dramatic for mobile |
| `titleLarge` | `20px` | `19px` | One notch down — feels more refined |
| `bodySmall` | `12px` | `12.5px` | Slightly more readable, especially for metadata |
| `labelMedium` | `12px, w500` | `11.5px, w600` | Tighter, bolder labels for pills/chips |

> [!NOTE]
> These are subtle (half-pixel) adjustments. The biggest impact comes from **letter-spacing**: add `letterSpacing: 0.1` to `labelMedium` and `labelLarge` for chip/pill text. It opens up small text beautifully.

