## 6. Screen-by-Screen Enhancements

### 6.1 Dashboard Screen

```mermaid
graph TB
    subgraph Current
        A["Hero Banner<br/>✅ Good gradient"]
        B["Stats Grid 2x2<br/>⚠️ Flat, no shadow"]
        C["Today's Schedule Cards<br/>⚠️ Dense metadata text"]
    end
    
    subgraph Enhanced
        D["Hero Banner<br/>+ softer shadow<br/>+ animated greeting"]
        E["Stats Grid 2x2<br/>+ white bg + soft shadow<br/>+ icon bg circles"]
        F["Schedule Timeline<br/>+ left accent line<br/>+ cleaner metadata chips"]
    end
    
    A --> D
    B --> E
    C --> F
```

#### Changes:

| Component | Enhancement | Effort |
|---|---|---|
| **Hero Banner** | Add subtle entrance animation (fade + slide up 8px over 300ms). Reduce shadow blur from 20→24, opacity from 0.22→0.18. | Small |
| **Insight Cards** | Change from `cardSurface` background to pure `white`. Add `AppShadow.card` instead of border-only. Add a soft color wash behind the icon circle (currently `14% opacity` → make it `10%` with a slightly larger circle `42×42`). | Small |
| **Schedule Cards** | Add a **3px left accent border** colored by status (green/blue/gray). This immediately communicates status without reading text. Remove the dense metadata string and replace with individual **metadata chips** (like the schedule screen already does). | Medium |
| **Empty State** | Use a softer illustration-style icon. Add a gentle pulse animation to the icon. | Small |
| **Section Headers** | Add a subtle fade-in stagger when content loads (each card appears 40ms after the previous). | Small |

#### Dashboard Schedule Card — Before vs After:

```diff
